Problems Fixed
--------------

The introduction of reproducible results from a change in the use of
random numbers has decreased the differences between results from
different platforms.

  DEC: optim:     ISO: T02.hadron: crash not seen, but Large_N crashed so
                                   we still have a problem.

 Large_N problem no longer seen in geant4-02-00-ref-02

  DEC: debug:    ISO: T13: *** Error in G4HEInelastic::GenerateNBodyEvent
                           total mass (1.87784) >= total energy (1.81268)
                     

New Problems and Features
-------------------------

The introduction of the g3tog4 tests gives rise to an indefinite loop of
prompting for input (which typically terminates after some hours when the
entire storage space for the output logs is exhausted). 
It was therefore, essential to avoid running g3tog4 tests on such platforms.

Having provided a mechanism, it seemed pointless to keep running test11 and
test15 on DEC "iso compliant" which fail (re-reading) files and for which 
the authors have no immediate intention of circumventing the compiler
problems.

